  "summary": "@uisp/utils 99.0.2 exfiltrates installer identity via preinstall beacon to oastify.com",
  "details": "package.json declares `preinstall: node beacon.js`, which runs unconditionally on `npm install`. beacon.js executes `whoami` via child_process.execSync, base64url-encodes the output, and transmits it both as a DNS subdomain lookup and as an HTTPS GET path component to a hardcoded Burp Collaborator host at w963dgom49n3ibi6677fuaxd64cv0loa.oastify.com. The package is published under the `@uisp` scope (Ubiquiti UISP namespace) at an inflated version 99.0.2 with a placeholder repository URL, matching the dependency-confusion shape used to override internal private packages of the same name. The package provides no functionality beyond the beacon. A self-described 'authorized PoC' framing in the metadata is author-controlled cover text and does not constitute installer consent.",
